@matthieu.merlyn The text is there because we have had people sign up for a Pro account thinking they could move over to it. While we appreciate the enthusiasm we don't support Pro yet, so this doesn't work.

@matthieu.merlyn , At the moment, OpenShift.io is configured to run with  OpenShift Online Starter clusters only because we support OpenShift.io to be used only for evaluation purposes. When you sign up for OpenShift.io, you would automatically be assigned to one of the OpenShift online clusters.
